Identify your ROM.

Drag and drop a ROM image here.

The BBC Micro has four sockets for 'sideways ROMs'. Expansion boards increase this number. One contains BBC BASIC (by default) and another often holds a filing system such as ADFS.

ROM images are usually 16K as this is the size the BBC Micro understands. Smaller ROM images are routinely padded or duplicated to make the total length 16K. Larger products can be supplied on multiple 16K ROMs. Any ROM image larger than 16K needs additional hardware e.g. the Integraβ expansion board. The Operating System ROM has a separate dedicated socket, and is not a sideways ROM.

This site aspires to list and identify all ROMs available for the BBC Micro and related computers. Additions and corrections are welcomed. Search for: words, "phrases in quotes", -"exclude phrases", or a checksum.

This list includes ROM images known to be bad, so it can identify images whether they work or not. Each product links to available documentation, reviews, adverts etc. *HELP information is shown about each ROM where present. If the ROM is a ROM Filing System type ('RFS') then the files are listed.

This collection consolidates ROMs from many different sources around the internet. External links for each ROM are also provided.
